  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (2026-Q1 model baseline)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Model baseline updated to 2026-Q1 incorporating revised impeller geometry tolerances; governing requirement continues to reference ASME V&V 40-2018 without acknowledgement of the 2022 addendum that revised hemolysis-index acceptance criteria.",
